               <p>EDWARD WARNER. I am a <rs id="t18260914-303-viclabel1716" type="occupation">brass-worker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-303-victim1640 t18260914-303-viclabel1716"></join>. On Sunday, the 10th of September, about one o'clock in the day, a handkerchief was taken from my coat pocket; I did not feel it taken, but was told it was gone - I turned and pursued the prisoner, who was running about fifty paces from me; he was taken but not in my sight.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-303-person1641">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HOLLIDAY
               <interp inst="t18260914-303-person1641" type="surname" value="HOLLIDAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-303-person1641" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-303-person1641" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a writer. I was behind this gentleman, and saw the prisoner approach his pocket; he then left it put something under his coat, and ran away - a person behind the prosecutor stepped up to him, and said, "Sir, that lad has your pocket-handkerchief" - I ran round the new-church to meet the prisoner, and took him; but the handkerchief had been previously dropped; I did not see him drop it.</p>
